---
---

<section id="ghampus" class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent via-[#0a0f1f] to-transparent">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center mb-12">
      <!-- Graphnosis logo above the chip — anchors the brand at the top
           of the hero so the Ghampus chip reads as a sub-product mark
           rather than a standalone title. -->
      <img src="/graphnosis-logo-transparent-bg.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="w-14 h-14 mx-auto mb-5 opacity-95" />

      <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center mb-6 px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-cyan-400/30 bg-cyan-400/5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-cyan-300">
        Ghampus
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-6">
        Your AI.
        <span
          class="block bg-clip-text text-transparent mt-2"
          style="background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #06b6d4 100%);"
        >Already on it.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-[#a5f3fc] leading-relaxed font-medium mb-4">
        Watches your memory grow. Walks your playbook. Checks in. Reports back. Local and encrypted.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Ghampus does for your second brain what your hippocampus does for your first. Taps into your facts, retrieves the right memory at the right moment, walks the SOPs your team already trained, decides what to attend to from everything that arrived overnight. Works the same memory and the same MCP tools every external client sees — Claude Desktop, Cursor, Copilot — but runs entirely on your machine. Free, Pro, Teams, Enterprise — all have access. Higher tiers add more discipline.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mt-12">

      <!-- Pillar 1: Proactive -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] p-6">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🤖</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Proactive, not reactive</h3>
        <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-sm leading-relaxed">
          "While you were away" surfaces what arrived overnight: connector pulls, AI client saves, shared-engram editor writes from collaborators. "Picking up where we left off" surfaces the memories Ghampus saved in prior sessions. Walks the right skill SOP the moment it matches what you're working on, before you have to find it yourself.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Pillar 2: Model routing -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] p-6">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🎯</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Pick the right model per step</h3>
        <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Skills declare what each step needs — reasoning, structured output, citations, code, vision. The router picks the cheapest available model that meets the constraints. Free local for routine steps, paid API only when the step truly needs it. Cost preview before every paid walk. Sensitive engrams are hard-locked to local-only — no remote provider sees a token of them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Pillar 3: File attachments -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] p-6">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">📎</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Link files without ingesting them</h3>
        <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Attach a PDF, image, spreadsheet, OneNote URI — anything — to a memory. The file stays where it is on your disk or shared drive; Graphnosis stores only the path. Recall surfaces it as a "Linked file" card, one click opens the original in its native app. SHA-256 content hashes survive file moves; the "Find new location…" button re-links anything that moved.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Savings + IT controls callout -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-emerald-400/30 bg-emerald-400/5 p-6">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">💸</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">What Graphnosis saves you</h3>
        <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Every successful recall is a paid LLM call that didn't have to happen. Ghampus logs the counterfactual: "this prompt would have cost $X at baseline rates." 30-day savings dashboard with per-event-kind breakdown. The dollar value of having a memory layer at all — finally measurable.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-violet-400/30 bg-violet-400/5 p-6">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🏛</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Enterprise model control</h3>
        <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-sm leading-relaxed">
          IT admins can disable providers (compliance), pin negotiated rates per-provider or per-model, and enforce policies that individual users can't override. AI credit pools (Azure, Bedrock, Copilot's new credits model) are first-class — track real spend against real budgets, not premium-call quotas.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-12">
      <a href="/ghampus/" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-white bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-cyan-500 hover:from-emerald-400 hover:to-cyan-400 transition-colors">
        See Ghampus in action →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
